linenoise
------------------------------------------
A minimal, zero-config, BSD licensed, readline replacement used in Redis,
MongoDB, and Android.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.7-1
  liblinenoise-devel-2.0-1bl1
  liblinenoise0-2.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/antirez/linenoise

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/antirez/linenoise/archive/refs/tags/2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack linenoise-2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./linenoise-2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/linenoise-2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/linenoise-2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblinenoise0-2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblinenoise-devel-2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(linenoise)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/linenoise.README
  /usr/share/doc/linenoise/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/linenoise/README.markdown

(liblinenoise0)
  /usr/bin/cyglinenoise-0.dll

(liblinenoise-devel)
  /usr/include/linenoise.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/linenoise/linenoiseConfig.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/linenoise/linenoiseConfigVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/linenoise/linenoiseTargets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/linenoise/linenoiseTargets.cmake
  /usr/lib/liblinenoise.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/linenoise.pc

